This journey helps you choose your final theme before starting your 6-month field immersion.</span></div><div style="font-weight: bold;"><br></div><b>Goal:</b></span> Equip you to listen and engage in the field<br><br><em data-end="532" data-start="522"><b>Mode: </b>Field&nbsp;<br><br><b>Evaluation: </b>Participation in site visits, understanding of field protocols, reflection on themes, and readiness to choose immersion track</em></div>" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=right;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="10" y="400" width="300" height="180" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-15" style="rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-7" target="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-14"> <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-7" value="<span style="text-align: right;">Week 2</span>" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="320" y="440" width="80" height="80" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-13" value="<b>Explore</b><div><br><span data-end="707" data-start="698"><span style="font-size: 12px;">Live for 30 days in the field as a volunteer, alongside people who work closely with nature or rural systems—like farmers, forest workers, or others in your chosen theme—no laptops—just your senses and a notebook.</span><br><b><br>Goal:&nbsp;</b></span>&nbsp;Live like a local. Work in the field. Understand the system.<br><br><em data-start="522" data-end="532"><b>Mode:</b> Field work<br><br><div><b>Evaluation: </b>Immersion quality, observation depth, engagement with locals, and field journal reflections</div><div><br></div></em></div>" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="490" y="560" width="300" height="180" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-24" style="rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-14" target="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-21"> <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-14" value="<span style="text-align: right;">Week 3-6</span>" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="400" y="600" width="80" height="80" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-26" style="rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-21" target="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-25"> <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-21" value="<span style="text-align: right;">Week 7-8</span>" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="320" y="760" width="80" height="80" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-22" value="<b>Reflect</b><div><br><div><span style="font-size: 12px;">After living in the field, you take time to pause and think. You revisit what you saw, felt, and heard—looking for patterns, pain points, and open questions. With mentor support, you turn those raw experiences into one clear problem that you deeply understand and are ready to work on.</span></div><div><br></div><strong data-start="698" data-end="707">Goal:</strong> &nbsp;Find the one problem that truly matters—with mentor support and a clear process.<br><br><em data-end="532" data-start="522"><b>Mode: </b>Classroom<br><b><br></b><div><b>Evaluation: </b>Depth of insight, clarity of problem framing, use of field experience, and reflection quality</div><div><br></div></em></div>" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=right;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="10" y="740" width="300" height="180" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-23" value="<b>Prequalification Round 2</b><div><br><div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;">Use what you experienced in Round 1 to pick one real problem that stood out to you. You’ll be placed into a team by the organizers to explore the problem, come up with ideas, and build a basic solution—just like in an ideathon. The round ends with a pitch to mentors.</span></div><div><br></div></div><strong data-start="487" data-end="496">Goal:</strong> Problem Ownership + First Steps of Solution<br data-start="519" data-end="522"><br><em data-start="522" data-end="532"><b>Mode: </b>Sprint&nbsp;<br><br><div><b>Evaluation: </b>Relevance of problem selected, teamwork, quality of ideas, clarity of pitch, and solution potential</div><div><br></div></em></div>" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="490" y="230" width="310" height="180" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-29" style="rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-25" target="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-28"> <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-25" value="<span style="text-align: right;">Week 9</span>" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="400" y="920" width="80" height="80" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-27" value="<b>Solve: Part 1 – Hackathon</b><div><br><span data-end="707" data-start="698"><div style=""><div>Start with an intensive week-long hackathon to focus on your selected problem. Work with your team to deeply understand the problem, frame it clearly, and explore possible solutions. This phase is about translating your insight into an actionable idea.</div><div><br></div></div><b>Goal:&nbsp;</b></span>Understand your problem deeply and frame a practical solution idea.<br><br><em data-start="522" data-end="532"><b>Mode:</b> Sprint + Collaboration<br><br><b>Evaluation:</b> Clarity of problem statement, originality of idea, team collaboration, and solution potential</em></div>" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="490" y="870" width="300" height="180" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-33" style="rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-28" target="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-31"> <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-28" value="<span style="text-align: right;">Week 10-13</span>" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="320" y="1080" width="80" height="80" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-30" value="<b>Solve: Part 2.1 – Build the Basics&nbsp;<br></b><span style="background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));">Translate your idea into a basic, working prototype. Focus on technical design and early field feedback.</span><div><br data-end="593" data-start="590"></div><strong data-end="602" data-start="593">Goal:</strong> Create a functional prototype and validate core assumptions.<br><br><strong data-end="675" data-start="666">Mode:</strong> Field Testing + Mentorship<br data-end="705" data-start="702"><br><b>Evaluation:</b> Technical feasibility, clarity of prototype logic, response to early field feedback, and consistency in weekly progress" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=right;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="10" y="1040" width="300" height="180" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-34" style="rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-31" target="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-32"> <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-31" value="<span style="text-align: right;">Week 14-17</span>" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="400" y="1240" width="80" height="80" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-39" style="rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-32" target="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-37"> <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-32" value="<span style="text-align: right;">Week 18-21</span>" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="320" y="1400" width="80" height="80" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-35" value="<div><b>Solve: Part 2.2 – Improve and Test</b></div><div><br></div><div><div>Refine your prototype using feedback. Test usability, performance, and user response in real-world settings.</div></div><div><br></div><strong data-end="912" data-start="903">Goal:</strong> Strengthen your solution through real-world testing and iteration.<br><br><strong data-end="991" data-start="982">Mode:</strong> Piloting + Expert Feedback<br><br><b>Evaluation: </b>Usability, performance improvements, responsiveness to user feedback, and effectiveness of field testing" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="490" y="1190" width="300" height="180" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-36" value="<div><b>Solve: Part 2.3 – Finalize and Prepare</b></div><div><br></div><div><div>Complete the final version of your solution. Focus on documentation, improvements, and preparing for implementation.</div></div><div><br></div><strong data-end="1241" data-start="1232">Goal:</strong> Deliver a ready-to-deploy solution with supporting documentation.<br><br><strong data-end="1319" data-start="1310">Mode:</strong> Final Validation + Peer &amp; Mentor Review<br><br><div><b>Evaluation: </b>Solution completeness, readiness for deployment, quality of documentation, and peer/mentor validation</div><div><br></div>" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=right;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="10" y="1350" width="300" height="180" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-42" style="rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;exitX=0.5;exitY=1;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" source="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-37" target="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-40"> <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-37" value="<span style="text-align: right;">Week 22-25</span>" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="400" y="1560" width="80" height="80" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-38" value="<div><b>Implement</b><b><br><br></b></div><div><div><div>Deploy your solution in the real world. Test it in the actual setting, gather feedback from users, improve it further, and prepare it for long-term use. Work with local people and institutions to ensure it can live beyond you.</div><div><br></div></div></div><div><b>Goal:</b> Deliver a usable, reliable solution with real-world feedback, documentation, and handoff.<br><br></div><div><b>Mode:</b> Field Deployment + Partner Collaboration<br><br></div><div><div><b>Evaluation: </b>Real-world usability, user adoption, quality of improvements, completeness of documentation, and readiness for transfer or scale</div><div><br></div></div>" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="490" y="1540" width="300" height="180" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-40" value="<span style="text-align: right;">Week 26-27</span>" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="320" y="1720" width="80" height="80" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-41" value="<div><b>Showcase<br><br></b></div><div><div><div>Present your journey, solution, and impact to a live audience of peers, mentors, and partners. Share what you built, what changed, and how others can carry it forward.</div><div><br></div></div></div><strong data-end="288" data-start="279">Goal:</strong> Celebrate your work, document your impact, and open paths for scale.<br><br data-end="360" data-start="357"><strong data-end="369" data-start="360">Mode:</strong> Public Presentation + Peer &amp; Partner Interaction<br><br data-end="421" data-start="418"><div><b>Evaluation: </b>Clarity of presentation, strength of impact story, audience engagement, and potential for scale or replication</div><div><br></div>" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=right;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="10" y="1700" width="300" height="180" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-43" value="" style="endArrow=none;html=1;rounded=0;entryX=0.5;entryY=1;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1" target="Beit7Q53fzd5peJJyGdC-40"> <mxGeometry width="50" height="50" relative="1" as="geometry"> <mxPoint x="440" y="1920" as="sourcePoint" /> <mxPoint x="410" y="1830" as="targetPoint" /> </mxGeometry> </mxCell> </root> </mxGraphModel> </diagram> </mxfile>

After living in the field, you take time to pause and think. You revisit what you saw, felt, and heard—looking for patterns, pain points, and open questions. With mentor support, you turn those raw experiences into one clear problem that you deeply understand and are ready to work on.
Goal: Find the one problem that truly matters—with mentor support and a clear process.
Mode: Classroom
Evaluation: Depth of insight, clarity of problem framing, use of field experience, and reflection quality

Use what you experienced in Round 1 to pick one real problem that stood out to you. You’ll be placed into a team by the organizers to explore the problem, come up with ideas, and build a basic solution—just like in an ideathon. The round ends with a pitch to mentors.
Goal: Problem Ownership + First Steps of Solution
Mode: Sprint
Evaluation: Relevance of problem selected, teamwork, quality of ideas, clarity of pitch, and solution potential

Start with an intensive week-long hackathon to focus on your selected problem. Work with your team to deeply understand the problem, frame it clearly, and explore possible solutions. This phase is about translating your insight into an actionable idea.
Goal: Understand your problem deeply and frame a practical solution idea.
Mode: Sprint + Collaboration
Evaluation: Clarity of problem statement, originality of idea, team collaboration, and solution potential

Solve: Part 2.1 – Build the Basics
Translate your idea into a basic, working prototype. Focus on technical design and early field feedback.
Goal: Create a functional prototype and validate core assumptions.
Mode: Field Testing + Mentorship
Evaluation: Technical feasibility, clarity of prototype logic, response to early field feedback, and consistency in weekly progress

Solve: Part 2.2 – Improve and Test
Refine your prototype using feedback. Test usability, performance, and user response in real-world settings.
Goal: Strengthen your solution through real-world testing and iteration.
Mode: Piloting + Expert Feedback
Evaluation: Usability, performance improvements, responsiveness to user feedback, and effectiveness of field testing

Solve: Part 2.3 – Finalize and Prepare
Complete the final version of your solution. Focus on documentation, improvements, and preparing for implementation.
Goal: Deliver a ready-to-deploy solution with supporting documentation.
Mode: Final Validation + Peer & Mentor Review
Evaluation: Solution completeness, readiness for deployment, quality of documentation, and peer/mentor validation

div.div: Deploy your solution in the real world. Test it in the actual setting, gather feedback from users, improve it further, and prepare it for long-term use. Work with local people and institutions to ensure it can live beyond you.
Goal: Deliver a usable, reliable solution with real-world feedback, documentation, and handoff.
Evaluation: Real-world usability, user adoption, quality of improvements, completeness of documentation, and readiness for transfer or scale

Showcase
Present your journey, solution, and impact to a live audience of peers, mentors, and partners. Share what you built, what changed, and how others can carry it forward.
Goal: Celebrate your work, document your impact, and open paths for scale.
Mode: Public Presentation + Peer & Partner Interaction
Evaluation: Clarity of presentation, strength of impact story, audience engagement, and potential for scale or replication
